Kenya Market Regulator Begins Probe Into CMC Directors’ Dispute

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-09-15T11:47:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/kenya-market-regulator-begins-probe-into-cmc-directors-dispute.html
Kenya’s  Capital Markets Authority 
began a probe into a dispute between directors of  CMC Holdings
Ltd. (CMCH) , the country’s biggest publicly traded auto dealership,
said Kungu Gatabaki, chairman of the regulator.  The authority also urged the company to appoint independent
directors to avoid similar disputes in future, Gatabaki told
reporters today in Nairobi.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  